    "narrative": "For April 16, 2026, the Ghost Ride the WHIP lineup is anchored by **Tyler Soderstrom** (76.91) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (76.21), both of whom benefit from favorable conditions against middle-of-the-road arms. **Tyler Soderstrom** is our strongest play, leveraging a massive 10% park boost and a +10% SP skill adjustment against Jack Leiter to maximize his power ceiling in the 4-hole. Similarly, **Vinnie Pasquantino** draws a premier spot in the order against Keider Montero; the combination of a favorable park and dynamic platoon splits against the right-hander makes him an essential start. **Mickey Moniak** also jumps into elite territory (75.75) due to the high-upside matchup against Ryan Weiss, where his platoon advantage and batting order stability create the highest pure ceiling among our outfielders today.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the optimizer involved the final utility and bench spots. **Zach McKinstry** (49.19) was the primary candidate for entry, nearly displacing **Kyle Karros** (50.77). While **Zach McKinstry** received a marginal boost from the platoon advantage against Kris Bubic, his lower base projection and the relative weakness of the opposing SP kept him just outside the active roster. We are also monitoring the lineup status of **Brice Turang** (63.08); while his base projection is solid, his value is heavily buoyed by an 86% SB-favorable environment against Patrick Corbin. If **Brice Turang** or other pending hitters drop in the batting order once official lineups are released, we risk a further erosion of their efficiency scores.\n\nRisks today are concentrated in the bottom of the order and our catching position. **Luis Campusano** (43.78) remains a marginal play; with his projected #8 spot and a tough matchup against Luis Castillo, he is hovering dangerously close to our \"below floor\" threshold. Furthermore, **James Wood** (55.42) faces a headwind regarding SB efficiency, as his matchup against Braxton Ashcraft features an elite hold pitcher who limits steal attempts. As we manage our game caps, we are keeping **Corbin Carroll**, **Austin Riley**, and **Seiya Suzuki** on the bench due to scheduled off-days, ensuring our active resources are strictly deployed against the most exploitable matchups on the board.",
